---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔄 Convert Python Object to JSON

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 json.dumps()

Converts a Python object into a JSON string.

---

# 💻 Example

```python id="json_dumps"
import json

student = {
    "name": "Saakshi",
    "age": 22
}

json_data = json.dumps(student)

print(json_data)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="dumps_output"
{"name": "Saakshi", "age": 22}
```

---

📌 Check Data Type

```python id="type_check"
print(type(student))

print(type(json_data))
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="type_output"
<class 'dict'>
<class 'str'>
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔄 Convert JSON to Python Object

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 json.loads()

Converts a JSON string into a Python object.

---

💻 Example

```python id="json_loads"
import json

data = '''
{
    "name":"Alex",
    "age":21
}
'''

student = json.loads(data)

print(student)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="loads_output"
{'name': 'Alex', 'age': 21}
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📄 Writing JSON to File

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 json.dump()

Writes a Python object to a JSON file.

---

💻 Example

```python id="json_dump"
import json

student = {
    "name": "Saakshi",
    "course": "Python"
}

with open(
    "student.json",
    "w"
) as file:

    json.dump(
        student,
        file
    )
```

---

📌 Generated File

```json id="student_json"
{
    "name": "Saakshi",
    "course": "Python"
}
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

📖 Reading JSON File

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔹 json.load()

Reads JSON data from a file.

---

💻 Example

```python id="json_load"
import json

with open(
    "student.json",
    "r"
) as file:

    data = json.load(file)

print(data)
```

---

▶️ Output

```text id="load_output"
{'name': 'Saakshi', 'course': 'Python'}
```

